    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-03-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-03-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="609"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d609">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/1066.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Nuevo Laredo</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nuevo Laredo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-03-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 26, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In expectation of an attack the Federal troops were in arms all last night, but
                    they offered no protection to this consulate. On the American side United States
                    troops were on guard to stop passage of revolutionists. What steps must be taken
                    in case consulate is threatened and no protection be given me by Federals?
                    Revolutionists probably not numerous enough to attack, but lawless element will
                    probably join for the chance to rob.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
